What you need to know:  Khaaliqa made history as the youngest Kenyan to have represented the country at a multi-sport event at the age of 12 in the 2010 Delhi Commonwealth GamesKhaaliqa, who is now 24, missed the 2014 Glasgow Commonwealth Games but made a return at the 2018 Gold Coast Games alongside Hardeep Reel in the men's eventKhaaliqa will team up with newcomer Violet Luchendo in the women’s event while Muqtadir Nimji and James Dalidi will represent Kenya in the men’s competition